Leadership. I was speaking to someone recently that was frustrated people weren’t following them, so here is a good question we should all ask OURSELVES, do the people that we want to follow us WANT TO GO WHERE I AM GOING ? Translation are you an example ? And not just financially (although that is important) , how is your work ethic , attitude , do you have integrity ? All of these are places we can check ourselves and out fruit 🍎 🍉 .

Are you following a follower OR a you following a leader ? The truth is we typically all follow someone…. But we must also lead. In the midst of following we must also inspect what we expect in the FRUIT 🍎 of those we are following. Wouldn’t it be scary if you were following someone and they were confused why you were copying them, or even asking for advice ? It happens more often then you know…

The process… the part that we try to rush that makes it all the more enjoyable…. I remember I used to play this game called Gran Turismo as a kid and one day I was tired of trying, so I went to Kroger and bought a magazine called tips and tricks (only older gamers know this) anyway in the magazine it gaze me the code for unlimited money, unlimited upgrades, and all the cars were unlocked… I was excited unlocked the game… less than a week later I never played it again..
-
That day I realized that apart of the journey that makes it worthwhile and fun to enjoy is the process aka the journey… it’s the journey, the people you meet, the experiences, learning yourself, bouncing back from the wins and losses, to achieve even more. That’s what I love most!

Best of #2022 and it still applies !Don’t compare yourself to other folks, some of these folks got ppp loans… Please don’t start scamming, ripping off customers, or worse…. It’s a time to re evaluate your skills, reset and come back stronger than ever. Don’t QUIT BEING AN ENTREPRENEUR, instead learn the lessons from it. And if you have a family take care of your family. OR BUILD YOUR BUSINESS that’s literally your options. Here's are potential ways to handle it: 

1. Set boundaries: Clearly define your limits and communicate them assertively. Establishing boundaries will help protect your well-being and maintain your self-respect.

2. Focus on self-care: Prioritize your own mental and emotional well-being. Engage in activities that bring you joy, seek support from friends or professionals, and practice self-care routines to maintain a healthy mindset.

3. Seek support: Share your experiences with trusted friends or seek guidance from a therapist who can provide insights and strategies for dealing with a narcissistic individual.

4. Practice assertiveness: Stand up for yourself and express your needs and concerns clearly and confidently. Assertive communication can help you navigate interactions with a narcissistic woman more effectively.

5. Consider distancing yourself: In certain situations, maintaining distance or limiting contact with a narcissistic woman may be necessary for your own well-being. Prioritize your mental health and make choices that serve your long-term happiness.
